commit.message:
Add Haddock docs to parts of the public API

Co-authored-by: Leopold Wigbratt <leopoldwigbratt@users.noreply.github.com>
Parse: Avoid backtracking in pDictExpr

Test: Add regression test for #43/#45
A compiler test (spread-09) has been adjusted but still fails, but this is due to another error. Will submit an issue about this soon.

Parse: Allow colon in dict literal
':' should always be allowed in the start of a dictionary definition.
See #43 and #45

Support grid.(cell,header,footer,hline,vline).

Closes #44.

Support table.(cell,vline,hline,header,footer).

See #44.  I think we need these for grid as well.

Parse: allow space after equation in code.

This also fixes the bug noted above in parsing
raw content in code.

See #43.

Parse: lexeme now treats unicode whitespace characters as whitespace.

See #43.

Parser: Allow raw (backticked) content as code expression.

See #43.

Note: there is still a bug.  For some reason, parsing
`` #let x = `hello` `` gives us the let binding and then
a literal verbatim `hello`.
Parser: allow colon in label. See #43.

Parser: allow line comments at end of file...

with no final newline. See #43.
Depend on typst-symbols 0.1.6.
Bump to 0.5.0.2, update changelog

Fix parsing of field access in math.

`$plus.circle_2$` should give you a subscript 2 on the
symbol `plus.circle`.  Underscores are not allowed in
field access in math. Closes #41.
Support toml-parser-2.0.0.0
Bump version to 0.5.0.1, update changelog.

Set evalPackageRoot to working dir to start...

even if the file to be converted is somewhere else.
Anyway, this seems to be what the test suite expects.

Make file loading relative to package root if present.

Closes #39.

Parser: remove pBindExpr from pBaseExpr.

This does not seem to be necessary, and it causes problems
with things like `$#x = $y$`. Closes #34.

Fix assignment of module name in package imports.

Closes #30.

Don't allow container.at to insert new values.

Closes #26.

Handle `dict.at(variable) = expression`.

Closes #25.

Remove dependency on the unmaintained digits library.

We just copy the code for the function we need (with
attribution): it is BSD3-licensed.

Closes #24.
Bump to 0.5, update changelog.

Support "as" keyword in imports.

API change: in Typst.Syntax, the Imports type now contains
fields for an optional "as" identifier.

See #21.

Ensure that set rule doesn't pick up if on next line.

Closes #23.

Support version type.

API change: add VVersion constructor to Val, TVersion to ValType.

Support the `version` constructor function and the `at` method.

See #21.
Allo multiline strings (closes #20).

Allow function applications in dictionary key construction.

API change:  in Typst.Syntax, the Dict constructor for Expr
now takes type `[Spreadable (Expr, Expr)]` instead of
`[Spreadable (Identifier, Expr)]`. This is because the key
identifiers sometimes are not known at parse time and must
be computed in Evaluate.

Closes #19.
Update changelog.
